  [1m[38;2;122;162;247m[details][0m[38;2;192;202;245m[48;2;26;27;38m                                                                                                          [38;2;86;95;137m│[38;2;192;202;245m  
  The 404 is the gateway sending previous_response_id while store=false, and those two are mutually exclusive by     [38;2;86;95;137m│[38;2;192;202;245m  
  design. Server-side response chaining only works when the response was persisted, which is exactly what store=false[38;2;86;95;137m│[38;2;192;202;245m  
  turns off. So previous_response_id should not be on the request at all when store is false.                        [38;2;86;95;137m│[38;2;192;202;245m  
                                                                                                                     [38;2;86;95;137m│[38;2;192;202;245m  
  There are two separate defects here and the fix needs both.                                                        [38;2;86;95;137m│[38;2;192;202;245m  
